text.tspan: Maternal mortality ratio vs. GDP per capita, 2020
Maternal mortality ratio is the number of women who die from pregnancy-related causes while pregnant or within 42
days of pregnancy termination per 100,000 live births.
Data source: Gapminder (2010); WHO (2019); OECD (2022); Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: GDP per capita is measured in constant international-$ which adjusts for inflation and cross-country price differences.
